        </ul>
        <p>You <strong>may</strong> use the knowledge, techniques, configurations, and code examples from the Product in your own projects without restriction.</p>

        <h2>3. Payment</h2>
        <p>All payments are processed securely by Stripe. Prices are in US dollars. You agree to provide accurate billing information. All sales are one-time payments — there are no recurring charges unless you explicitly subscribe to a separate service.</p>

        <h2>4. Refund Policy</h2>
        <p>We offer a <strong>30-day money-back guarantee</strong> on all Products. If you are not satisfied with your purchase for any reason, contact us within 30 days of purchase for a full refund.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Refund requests should be sent to hello@erronatus.com</li>
          <li>Include your order confirmation or email address used for purchase</li>
          <li>Refunds are processed within 5-10 business days</li>
          <li>No reason required — we trust your judgment</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Product Delivery</h2>
        <p>Products are delivered electronically to the email address provided at checkout. Delivery is typically instant but may take up to 24 hours. If you haven't received your Product within 24 hours, check your spam folder and contact us at hello@erronatus.com.</p>

        <h2>6. Updates</h2>
        <p>Product updates are provided at our discretion. All editions include free updates to the purchased edition. We are not obligated to provide updates, but we intend to maintain and improve the Product over time.</p>

        <h2>7. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>The Product is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. Specifically:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The Product is educational content, not professional advice</li>
          <li>Trading-related content is for educational purposes and paper trading only — it is not financial advice</li>
          <li>We do not guarantee specific results, income, or outcomes</li>
          <li>Third-party APIs, services, and tools mentioned may change their terms, pricing, or availability</li>
          <li>OpenClaw is open-source software maintained by its own community — we are not affiliated with or responsible for OpenClaw's development</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, Erronatus shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the Website or Products. Our total liability shall not exceed the amount you paid for the Product.</p>

